<p>Each tested formulation containing 7 mg of cinnamon oil was calculated for application amount in each group and applied onto the induced infected skin area of the rats once daily for six days. Bodyweight and burn edge contraction by the circle wound diameter were measured daily before the application of the next dose. Wound contraction was expressed as a reduction in the percentage of original wound diameter using the following equation (Tavares Pereira et al., 
